33    /**
34    * A compiler pass that checks that the programmer has obeyed all the access
35    * control restrictions indicated by JSDoc annotations, like
36    * {@code @private} and {@code @deprecated}.
37    *
38    * Because access control restrictions are attached to type information,
39    * it's important that TypedScopeCreator, TypeInference, and InferJSDocInfo
40    * all run before this pass. TypedScopeCreator creates and resolves types,
41    * TypeInference propagates those types across the AST, and InferJSDocInfo
42    * propagates JSDoc across the types.
43    *
44    * @author nicksantos@google.com (Nick Santos)
45    */
